texts.text: >The temples and shrines that have protected this land spiritually.
>Just as acts of gratitude towards the gods, sound minds and a sense of pride also have.
>As these become lost, the power bestowed upon our temples and shrines begins to wane.
>Mara appeared and brought human evil and malice to the surface.
>Take-Minakata, a founding deity of this land, was luckily there
>to aid the Liberators in their fight against Mara...
I manifest from your own toxic desires, humans.
As long as those continue to exist, my poison will persist.
We will meet again, pathetic creatures!
Aaargh!
>Mara spits out something at Take-Minakata as it disappears.
Huh...!
>Take-Minakata writhes in pain as Mara's poison begins to consume him.
>A scale-like pattern begins to emerge as Take-Minakata
>begins to transform into an entirely different being.

*Pant*
We must go after it...
Take-Minakata...
Don't come closer!
Or I'll slice you...!
>The mysterious demon readies his sword while scanning his surroundings
>and carefully takes a few steps away from everyone.
Don't follow me.
>He dives into the ground and vanishes.
>The poison that seeks to devour this land still sleeps deep below the surface...
I've pursued him this deep, but what is this labyrinth...?
I need only follow the traces of evil I'm sensing... This way.
What is this...?!
>The stagnant air exudes an ominous aura...!
This cannot be... It's nothing like the poison that reached the surface.
If this were to be released, this land will surely be...
>A stream of evil flows outward
>and consumes Take-Minakata in the form of a whirlwind!
N-no... This can't...!
Gah...!! Aaargh...!
Aaahhhhhhhh!!
>In a residential area someplace...
>A group of people are chatting in front of the entrance to a condo building.
That's really too bad. They came so late because he lived alone, right?
They said that someone on the same floor said there was an awful smell.
Did they have any kids or relatives?
Not sure... I only ever passed them by in the hallway.
Wait... When did that lecture start again...?
During the previous week, an elderly person was found alone in their room, dead.
I just brushed it off like nothing ever happened.
I happened to see them from time to time
and just happened to live nearby them.
Would anyone honestly be bothered by something like that?
The train is arriving on Platform 2. Please stand behind the yellow line...
Times like these, I'm always reminded of something.
That time when my classmate was being bullied in middle school.
It's not like I felt good by watching it happen,
but no one else, including me, ever said anything about it.
And one day, someone actually stood up to them.
My classmate thanked them while crying like a baby,
and the person who saved them was relieved it was over.
The next day...
The savior became the target for bullying.
There's just no point in dealing with people's bullshit.
So I've decided not to get involved with like that and avoid the stress.
Just go with the flow and attain happiness somehow.
Get by in life by picking low-hanging fruit.
Who cares how I live my life? Who cares how other people do?
Canceled...?

*Sigh*
I should've checked.
>At the campus of a university somewhere...
I need to kill some time before my next class... Oh, I need to log in.
Games it is...
But who would've known...
That someone like me would be thrown into the middle of this kind of mess.
I would never have thought...
Huh...?
Was that an earthquake? It feels pretty...
Big...
The ground below my feet suddenly vanished.
Not having any idea what'd just happened,
all I could do was scream my lungs out.
*Scream*
Yo, can y'all hear me?
That earthquake's causin' the ground to sink around Tokyo.
...is what the newscaster was sayin' but there's more to than just that.
Demons are comin' out of these holes yo.
I got a hold of Seiran just in case too.
Subsidence is takin' place close to the Dragon Stream.
But we won't get more info just sittin' around yo.
Y'all need to investigate what's goin' on at each site.
I'm headin' out with Newbie in a sec too.
Yo, the university nearby is lookin' bad, so we're hittin' that up first.
Y'all need to link up with anyone you can and see what's up.
Liberators, roll out!
>At the university...
>Chaos reigns as the students and staff scramble around...
Is this what they mean by hell on Earth?
Don't see any demons... Not yet at least.
Yo, we gotta check out that hole...
Wait...!!
Another quake?!
This is big... It's hard to keep balance...
No!
>You look towards Seiran,
>and then towards the gaping chasm that people are falling into...
>Demons emerge soon after...!
We need to help them!
Take care of the demons!
Help them? Yo, Newbie!
Take care of them? Yo, what do you plan on doin'?
Wait, no...!
>You dive straight into the gaping hole!
A leap of faith without a second through! That's a new one!
Uhh, that just sounds insane. I mean look at it...
No, Vince. It's more than insane. It's a death wish!
No kiddin'!
Hold on, don't say things like that!
Let's summon our demons and slowly make our way down.
But I can't deny that not looking first is really...
Stupid... But we got other things to worry about.
Yo, there's a lot of 'em! We gotta handle these first!
Let's go! Devil Download!
*Groan*
W-where am I...?
You're awake?
Are you hurt?
Huh? Oh, I'm... You're...
Y-yes. I'm okay. But...
Who are you? Also, where are we?
I... I was on campus and an earthquake... The ground...
Calm down.
You seem okay.
That's easier said than done.
No, wait... I'm hardly just okay...

*Groan*
Oww...
What the hell just happened?
>You see at least three other people besides the girl you're talking to.
>Another man is hunched over in the corner...
What is this place? Am I dreaming? Ugh, wake up already...!
>None of the others even try to wake the man...
Wake the man.
Keep an eye on the man.
>Everyone eyes each other cautiously without saying a word.
>You decide to try and wake the man.
>He's breathing and seems to have lost consciousness.
>You call out to him as you shake his shoulders.

*Groan*
Ah... Aaahhhhh!!
What the?! That hole... I fell...!!
Where are we?! What happened...?!
What is this? This can't be happening to me!
>You try to get the attention of the other four people.
We need to find a way out!
This place isn't safe!
A way out... Yeah!
No one's gonna come and help us even if we wait...
What?! What do you mean not safe?!
You know what's going on? I guess I'll just follow you then.
Me too...
Can't imagine anything good coming out of just sticking around...
>With caution, you make your way into the labyrinth...
